1
00:00:01,650 --> 00:00:04,140
Instructor: When you are working with data tables,

2
00:00:04,140 --> 00:00:06,573
you have to be careful about one thing.

3
00:00:07,440 --> 00:00:09,300
Number of columns that we have

4
00:00:09,300 --> 00:00:13,470
in product.js here cannot exceed the number of

5
00:00:13,470 --> 00:00:16,890
table header or DH that we have

6
00:00:16,890 --> 00:00:19,860
inside the CSS HTML.

7
00:00:19,860 --> 00:00:23,850
Right now you can see we have six columns right here

8
00:00:23,850 --> 00:00:25,530
in product.js.

9
00:00:25,530 --> 00:00:26,790
We have five.

10
00:00:26,790 --> 00:00:30,030
If you have less columns than the (indistinct)header,

11
00:00:30,030 --> 00:00:31,530
that is okay.

12
00:00:31,530 --> 00:00:34,170
But if I add more columns here

13
00:00:34,170 --> 00:00:36,993
let me copy and paste that once again.

14
00:00:37,920 --> 00:00:42,780
And if I go back here, that is also functional.

15
00:00:42,780 --> 00:00:45,300
It populated the same data here.

16
00:00:45,300 --> 00:00:47,820
But if I copy that one more time,

17
00:00:47,820 --> 00:00:51,000
now we have seven columns right here,

18
00:00:51,000 --> 00:00:53,820
and we have six columns in the view.

19
00:00:53,820 --> 00:00:58,710
If I save that, you can see it does not work in the console.

20
00:00:58,710 --> 00:01:01,053
We have an error right here.

21
00:01:02,130 --> 00:01:05,730
So always remember that columns must match.

22
00:01:05,730 --> 00:01:08,040
One column that I have left here is for

23
00:01:08,040 --> 00:01:09,780
edit and delete buttons.

24
00:01:09,780 --> 00:01:12,590
So basically we should only have five columns

25
00:01:12,590 --> 00:01:14,553
in product.js.

26
00:01:15,600 --> 00:01:17,760
Let me revert back the change here.

27
00:01:17,760 --> 00:01:20,520
If you want to add one more column here,

28
00:01:20,520 --> 00:01:24,693
you will also have to add a th element right here.

